<ul id="commtree_64482271"><li id="tree_64483557" class="comment oneline"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_64483557" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64483557" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64483557" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64483557" name="comment_link_64483557" href="//linux.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23327717&amp;cid=64483557" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64483557)" >Re:</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64483557" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64483557); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~codebase7">codebase7</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~codebase7">( 9682010 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64483557"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64483557">Samba <a href="https://wiki.samba.org/index.php/Samba_Security_Documentation#Windows_overview_documents" title="samba.org">doesn't enforce AD trusts properly<span class="substr"> </span></a> [samba.org] or <a href="https://wiki.samba.org/index.php/Active_Directory_Trusts" title="samba.org">perform filtering on Domain SIDs. (SID filtering rules are not applied!!!)</a> [samba.org] <br>
<br>
<a href="https://wiki.samba.org/index.php/SysVol_replication_(DFS-R)" title="samba.org">Samba doesn't support DFS replication</a> [samba.org], so if it serves Group Policies as a domain controller, client systems may have inconsistent policies applied to them.<br>
<br>
Samba cannot reliably enforce filesystem permissions due to improper ACL support in the kernel. <a href="https://wiki.samba.org/index.php/Samba_4.20_Features_added/changed#Allow_'smbcacls'_to_save/restore_DACLs_to_file" title="samba.org">To the point of needing it's own utilities to backup and restore them.</a> [samba.org] <br>
<br>
<a href="https://wiki.samba.org/index.php/Samba_4.20_Features_added/changed#Get_locally_logged_on_users_from_utmp" title="samba.org">Samba <i>lies</i> about the list of logged on users because implementin</a> [samba.org]</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64483557">

</div>
</div>

